.TH "vzalloc_node" 9 "vzalloc_node" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vzalloc_node \- allocate memory on a specific node with zero fill
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" vzalloc_node
.BI "(unsigned long size "  ","
.BI "int node "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "size" 12
allocation size
.IP "node" 12
numa node
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate enough pages to cover \fIsize\fP from the page level
allocator and map them into contiguous kernel virtual space.
The memory allocated is set to zero.
.SH "RETURN"
pointer to the allocated memory or NULL on error
